column5: Beautiful weekend up in the french. Slow bite but we managed a bunch of smaller walleye, lots of nice bass, lots of small pike, and a 46" musky which is now my wife's P.B. All fish were released except for 2 unlucky walleyes that were great in the frying pan. Great time had by all. Saw a bear and a small mink i think. Here are a couple pictures of the nicer fish we caught.
Sweet ... We just love that part of Ontario.
Awesome fish!  Not much better than spending a few days on the French
The section between Georgian Bay and HWY 69.
